<div class="wp-block-group has-global-padding is-content-justification-left is-layout-constrained wp-container-core-group-is-layout-bfce2198 wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained" style="padding-right:0;padding-left:0">
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">I started writing because I was afraid of how easily thoughts would disappear. Not the important—but the small ones. How light shifts when I leave a room. The sound of a page turning in the night.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Small observations. They don’t ask to be understood. Only to be recorded and maybe read, slowly.</p>



<div style="height:var(--wp--preset--spacing--small)" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">— Lucía M.</p>
</div>



